snippet.textDisplay:
MESAGE TO MIKEL ARTETA & ARSENAL PLAYERS. PLEASE READ THIS.
Since Arsene Wenger time, we have a habit of starting 2nd half slow. And we get hit there sometimes.

I know why.

It happens to us everyday, but we don't ever realize.

When your body is warm, & you sit down, you get cold.

To stop that...
DONT HOOK UP YUR FEET..
Don't sit with your legs folded...
KEEP YUR FEET STRETCHED OUT.
PREFERABLY THEY SUD SIT FLAT & GET SUM FLUID.

If you sit with knees bended,
Yur muscles will start to get cold, or shrink back or tighten.
& You have to loosen up again.
THATS WHY WE START SO SLOW IN 2ND HALF.

SIT WITH LEGS STRETCHED OUT...

SIT FLAT. KEEP YUR LEGS STRETCHED OUT.

REMEMBER, YOU GO IN AT HALF TIME, YOU GO INTO THE AIR CONDITION ROOM.

IF EVER YOU FOLD ANY PART OF YUR BODY/LIMBS, YUR MUSCLES START TO CONTRACT, THEY START TO RELAX, AND TIGHTEN.

KEEP YUR LEGS STRETCHED OUT.

SIT FLAT ON THE FLOOR.

YOU WONT NEED TO WARM UP AGAIN..

YOU WILL FEEL BETTER & MORE ENERGIZED.

AIN THAT HOW YOU REST AFTER RUNNING?

Looking at the Arsenal dressing room.

I'm wondering if when we go in at half time, the players go to their respective area and sit there..

I don't Kno what goes on at half time..

But.. it could be an area of neglegence by the players to just get off the field, & take a seat...

If so, you are setting yourself back..
Cud even pull a muscle when you get back.

For the 10 minutes half time talk.. keep the legs stretched out..

Get sum fluids.

Lay down flat if you must..

But never hook up any part of your body whilst you rest.
Never bend your legs.

Keep them stretched out, keep stretching.

Don't sit on the bench in the dressing rooms.

You get cold when you do.
& You won't feel it.
